communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

1. All FOIA taskers, processing notes, tracking sheets, or other agency records created, sent, or received by ICE FOIA in response to the FOIA request and appeal designated by ICE as 2022-ICAP-01053 and 2021-ICFO-04070. 

2. Any records of communication sent or received by ICE regarding the FOIA request assigned tracking numbers 2022-ICAP-01053 and 2021-ICFO-04070.

Thank you, 

Andrew Free
#DetentionKills Transparency Initiative 
Al Otro Lado

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Andrew Free

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

The subject of this request is Christine B. Stump, who is known to have been originally admitted to the West Virginia Bar through reciprocity on June 9, 1998. Pursuant to the WV Freedom of Information Act, we are requesting that you produce information regarding the original state of Christine B. Stump's bar admission, or the state of admission to practice law which the State of West Virginia based the grant of license for Ms. Stumps to practice law in the State of West Virginia.

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

All reports of significant FOIA activity received from all DHS component FOIA office by the DHS Privacy Office from January 1, 2013 - May 5, 2023. The responsive records are required for each DHS component FOIA office by the 2/9/2005 Chief Privacy Officer memo.

An example of a responsive document obtained through a prior request, which your office assigned tracking number 2022-HQFO-01117, is available here: 
https://s3.documentcloud.org/documents/23685324/dhs-significant-foia-activity-2022-hqfo-01117.pdf 

Thank you, 

Andrew Free
#DetentionKills Transparency Initiative
